<br>
I have been on these boards only a short period of time, and on more than one occasion I have read post where someone is going off the deep end telling the RP NAZIS and RP ELITISTS to back out of their life and let them play the way they want. Uh.. Hello.. You post a question, you get constructive, not violent, non personal feedback, and you go totally off the wall? Nobody said anything about playing any way. WTF? WHO is the Elitist? Who is trying to dictate? You don't want to hear anything but &quot;Yes, perfect, you are right.&quot; Nobody's opinion matters but your's? <br>
<br>
AND We're close minded? OMFG!  Get over yourselves. Just because someone's opinion doesn't move lock step with yours is no invitation to begin the personal attacks, perhaps you should consider that before asking for one.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isharramoonsong>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 711<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/10/02 6:51:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1977.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Why bother asking a RP question?</span><hr size=1> Listen, bud... if you haven't been reading here long, then  you haven't seen the mountains of posts by the &quot;RP Nazis&quot; damning anyone who doesn't play their way. My response was an overreaction based on the fact that the very same people who supposedly promote roleplay and want Firiona Vie to remain a roleplay server are all too happy to criticize any roleplay that doesn't match their world view. But, since you haven't been reading here long, you wouldn't know that, now would you?<br>
<br>
I'm not saying that a low post count makes your opinion  invalid. It just means that you haven't been around long enough to see roleplay stifled and people who are trying to roleplay stifled time and time again because people are too busy criticizing (and no, it is not always constructive) to dish out any sort of praise. <br>
<br>
My roleplay guide wasn't telling anyone *what* to roleplay. It was merely meant to give pointers to those who might. And I made it clear that it is all about fun in the end anyway. It was just a little something to offer to the roleplay newbies out there who might want to get their feet wet.<br>
<br>
Immediately, I get attacked for telling people how to RP. If my critics had read the goddamn thing from start to finish, you would see that I clearly state that I am not the be-all and end-all source for RP. <br>
<br>
But that's not good enough for people. Instead, people immediately started picking apart my examples and taking them completely out of context. Wtf? It was just a friendly post designed to *try* and spread some roleplay good will, and within three posts I get people not just stating their opinions, but completely attacking bits and pieces of the post without even mentioning any of the helpful parts. <br>
<br>
You and Caillou both just swarmed to one point and picked it apart, with little appreciation for the work I put into it as a whole. At least Grodash had the decency to mention that in general he appreciated the work I put into it even if he didn't agree with one part. But you and Caillou both immediately came out swinging for a fricking debate.<br>
<br>
But once again, it comes back to an attitude trend I've seen on here of late: RP isn't about what is fun for you nor is it about a player's own level of comfortability with roleplay. It's either you play their way, or you're not a good roleplayer. <br>
<br>
But you wouldn't know that, because you haven't been reading here for long, have you? I was not saying that my &quot;guide&quot; was anything more than tips, but the thread turned into a fucking debate over whether thoughts should be emoted or whether rolling back storylines is &quot;good roleplay.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, everyone is entitled to their own opinions, and I did ask for input, but I expected constructive responses, not fucking debate. But given the nature of this community, what else could I expect?<br>
<br>
Yes, Apep, you can stop the stopwatch now. <br>
<br>
And you, Dronk, can kiss my pretty white ass if you aren't satisfied with my response. <br>
<br>
